(41, 221, 110, 'De basis van de italiaanse keuken', '<h1 style="text-align: left; color: #ffffff; font-size: 26px; font-family: Georgia1,Georgia,serif; font-weight: bold; line-height: 160%;"><span style="color: #ffffff;">De basis van de Italiaanse keuken</span></h1>\n<p style="text-align: left; font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia1, Georgia, serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 140%;"><strong><span style="font-size: 14px; color: #b72025;">(om meer tekst te zien klik op tekst en scroll naar beneden met PgDown of pijltje)</span><br /></strong><br /><span style="color: #ffffff;"><strong>Cursus "Di16" op dinsdag 14/28 januari en 11/25 februari 2014 VOL<br />Cursus "Wo08" op woensdag 15/29 januari en 12/26 februari 2014<br /></strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left; font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia1, Georgia, serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 140%;"><span style="font-size: 14px; color: #ffffff;"><span style="color: #ffffff;"><strong>Cursus "Di17" op dinsdag 6/20 mei en 3/17 juni 2014 </strong></span></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left; font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia1, Georgia, serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 140%;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: left; font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia1, Georgia, serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 140%;"><span style="font-size: 14px; color: #ffffff;"><strong>Les 1: Antipasti en klassieke hapjes&nbsp;</strong></span><br /><span style="font-size: 14px; color: #ffffff;">Frittata, vleesballetjes in tomatensaus, crespelle met pesto rosso e mozzarella (kleine gevulde cr&ecirc;pes), focaccia, crema di olive (olijvencreme), gegratineerde paprika''s, crostini van polenta met gorgonzola en gefrituurde salie, rolletjes van rookvlees met truffelroomkaas en nog meer Italiaanse klassiekers.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left; font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia1, Georgia, serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 140%;"><span style="font-size: 14px; color: #ffffff;"><strong>Les 2: Pasta, gnocchi en sauzen&nbsp;</strong></span><br /><span style="font-size: 14px; color: #ffffff;">Pasta maken (technieken, trucjes, de beste ingredi&euml;nten en varianten, bijv. gekleurde en gevulde pasta), basissauzen (waaronder de pesto alla genovese en de bolognese), aardappelgnocchi maken.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left; font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia1, Georgia, serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 140%;"><span style="font-size: 14px; color: #ffffff;"><strong>Les 3: Brood, risotto en groente&nbsp;</strong></span><br /><span style="font-size: 14px; color: #ffffff;">Ciabatta maken (basis broodbereiding), zelf bouillon trekken (vegetarisch, vlees), saffraanrisotto met ossobuco alla milanese (gesmoorde kalfschenkel), risotto alle verdure di stagione (risotto met seizoensgroente), bijzondere groentebereidingen met speciale groentensoorten.</span></p>\n<p style="font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia1, Georgia, serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 140%;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-collapse: separate; font-family: ''American Typewriter''; line-height: normal; border-spacing: 0px; font-size: medium; color: #ffffff;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><strong>Les 4: Vis, vis en nog eens vis!&nbsp;<br /></strong></span><span style="font-size: 14px;">Vis herkennen, schoonmaken en fileren (visfilets in pittige wijnsaus), visfonds bereiden, inktvis schoonmaken en bereiden (gevulde inktvis), gamba&acute;s (gefrituurde gamba&acute;s in kataifideeg), sardientjes uit de oven met knoflook en kruiden, venusschelpen (spaghetti alle vongole).</span></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left; font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia1, Georgia, serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 140%;"><span style="font-size: 14px; color: #ffffff;">Alle kooklessen beginnen om 18.30 uur en eindigen rond 22.30 uur. De prijs voor deze cursussen is</span><br /><span style="font-size: 14px; color: #ffffff;"><strong>&euro; 295,00&nbsp;</strong>inclusief wijn- en drankenarrangement. Deze combinatie van lessen als cadeau geven kan: koop een cadeaubon voor een 4-weekse cursus! Binnenkort nog meer 4-weekse cursussen voor jan. - jun. 2014. Blijf deze website checken voor data.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left; font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia1, Georgia, serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 140%;"><span style="color: #ffffff;"><strong><span style="font-size: 14px;">Groepen:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style="font-size: 14px;">we werken in groepen van min. 4 en max. 14 personen. Als je op een bepaalde avond verhinderd bent, is het mogelijk om iemand anders aan de kookles te laten deelnemen. Wil je dat a.j.b. van tevoren met Nicoletta bespreken? Grazie!</span></span></p>\n<p style="font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia1, Georgia, serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 140%;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-collapse: separate; font-family: ''American Typewriter''; line-height: normal; border-spacing: 0px; font-size: medium; color: #ffffff;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><strong>Om een workshop of cursus te boeken stuur ons een mailtje (via "<a href="../../contact" target="_blank">Contact</a>" op deze site)</strong></span></span></p>', '5bd1b75687edad257b6f40d61ef84acc.jpg', '', '0000-00-00', 1, 0, 0, '2013-12-15 13:47:32'),
(44, 221, 110, 'De streekgebonden keuken', '<h1 style="color: #ffffff; font-size: 26px; font-family: Georgia1, Georgia, serif; font-weight: bold; line-height: 160%;">De Streekgebonden keuken</h1>\n<p style="font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia1, Georgia, serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 140%;"><span style="color: #ffa225;"><strong><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">(om meer tekst te zien klik op tekst en scroll naar beneden met PgDown of pijltje)</span></strong></span></p>\n<p style="margin-bottom: 14px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 140%; font-family: Georgia1, Georgia, serif; font-weight: normal;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0px; color: #ffffff;">Iedere Italiaanse streek heeft zeer uit elkaar verschillende eetgewoontes, recepten en ingredienten. In onze reis door Italie ontdekken we de keuken van <strong>Veneto, Lombardia, Campania en Lazio</strong> (mrt./apr. 2014) met gerechten als <strong>caponata</strong>, risotto alla milanese met <strong>ossobuco</strong>, <strong>Romeinse lamsstoofschotel</strong> met citroen, zoete gefrituurde ravioli met ricotta en citroen, een aubergine-kaastaartje uit de Noord-Italiaanse Renaissance, <strong><em>parmigiana di melanzane</em></strong>, <strong>mascarponecr&egrave;me</strong> met zelfgemaakte kattentongen, <strong>Venetiaanse vleesballetjes</strong>, polentakoekjes met sabayon en meer.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style="margin-bottom: 14px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 140%; font-family: Georgia1, Georgia, serif; font-weight: normal;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0px; color: #ffffff;">Tijdens iedere les maken we een 3-gangenmenu met 5 verschillende seizoensgerechten. Noord, Zuid en Centrum komen aan bod met al hun rijkdom aan smaken en variaties.<br /><br /> <strong>Cursus "Di18" op dinsdag 11/25 maart en 8/22 april 2014</strong>&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 140%; font-family: Georgia1, Georgia, serif; font-weight: normal;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0px; color: #ffffff;">Alle kooklessen beginnen om 18.30 uur en eindigen rond 22.30 uur. De prijs voor deze cursussen is&nbsp;</span><span style="letter-spacing: 0px; color: #ffffff;">&euro; 295,00 inclusief wijn- en drankenarrangement. Deze combinatie van lessen als cadeau geven kan: koop een cadeaubon voor een 4-weekse cursus! Binnenkort nog meer 4-weekse cursussen voor jan. - jun. 2014. Blijf deze website checken voor data.</span></p>\n<p style="margin-bottom: 14px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia1, Georgia, serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 140%;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0px; color: #ffffff; font-size: 14px;">Groepen: We werken in groepen van min. 4 en max. 14 personen. Als je op een bepaalde avond verhinderd bent, is het mogelijk om iemand anders aan de kookles te laten deelnemen. Wil je dat a.j.b. van tevoren met Nicoletta bespreken? Grazie!</span></p>\n<p style="font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia1, Georgia, serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 140%;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="margin-bottom: 14px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 140%; font-family: Georgia1, Georgia, serif; font-weight: normal;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0px; color: #ffffff;">Om een workshop of cursus te boeken stuur ons een mailtje (via "<span style="color: #ffa225;"><strong><a href="../../contact" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ffa225;">Contact</span></a></strong></span>" op deze site).</span></p>\n<p style="font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia1, Georgia, serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 140%;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0px; color: #ffffff;">&nbsp;</span></p>', '9ad59b78f05d6110e79b4cd917628e6e.jpg', '', '0000-00-00', 1, 1, 0, '2013-12-15 13:52:27'),
(45, 222, 110, 'The regional Italian cuisine', '<div class="gmail_extra">\n<h1 style="color: #ffffff; font-size: 26px; font-family: Georgia1,Georgia,serif; font-weight: bold; line-height: 160%;"><span style="color: #ffffff;"><strong>The regional italian cuisine</strong></span></h1>\n<p><span style="color: #000101;"><strong>(to see more text click on it and scroll down with PgDown or arrow)</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;<strong><br /></strong><span style="font-size: 14px;"><strong><strong>Course "Di18" on Tue. 11/26 March and 8/22 April 2014</strong></strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia1,Georgia,serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 140%;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">Every Italian region has very characteristic eating habits, recipes and ingredients. In our travel through Italy we discover the cuisine of </span><span style="font-size: 14px;"><strong>Veneto</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>Lombardia</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>Campania</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>Lazio</strong>&nbsp;(</span><span style="font-size: 14px;"><strong>course Di18</strong>&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 14px;">Mar./Apr. 2014) with dishes like </span><span style="font-size: 14px;"><strong><em>risotto alla milanese</em>&nbsp;</strong>with <strong>ossobuco</strong>, <strong>Roman stew</strong>&nbsp;with lamb meat and lemon, sweet&nbsp;<strong>fried ravioli</strong>&nbsp;with ricotta and lemon, an aubergine-cheese oven dish from the Northern Italian Renaissance, <strong><em>parmigiana di melanzane</em></strong>, mascarpone cream with&nbsp;<strong>home-made cat''s tongues</strong>, <strong>Venetian meatballs</strong>, polenta cookies with sabayon and a lot more.&nbsp;During every lesson we prepare a 3-course meal with 5 different seasonal dishes. North, South and Centre are well represented with all of their rich tastes and variations.</span></p>\n<p style="font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia1,Georgia,serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 140%;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia1,Georgia,serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 140%;"><strong style="font-size: 14px;">HOW, WHEN AND WHERE:</strong>&nbsp;All lessons start at 18.30 hrs. and end around 22.30 hrs. The courses are being held at cooking school La Cucina del Sole, Warmondstraat 180 in Amsterdam.</p>\n</div>\n<p style="font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia1,Georgia,serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 140%;">&nbsp;</p>\n<div class="gmail_extra">\n<p style="font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia1,Georgia,serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 140%;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">You can also give a course as a present: order a&nbsp;<strong>gift voucher</strong>&nbsp;for a cooking course through our Contact page!</span></p>\n<p style="font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia1,Georgia,serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 140%;">The&nbsp;<strong>price of this course is &euro;&nbsp;295,00</strong>&nbsp;including wine, all other drinks and all printed recipes.</p>\n<p><span style="font-size: 14px;">Keep on checking this website for new dates!</span></p>\n<p style="font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia1,Georgia,serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 140%;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p id="txt_131" style="font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia1,Georgia,serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 140%;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><strong>GROUPS</strong></span><br /><span style="font-size: 14px;">We work in groups with a minimum of 4 and a maximum of 14 participants.</span><br /><span style="font-size: 14px;">In case you miss a lesson it&rsquo;s not possible to come to another workshop later on. If you can&rsquo;t participate to one specific lesson, you can send a friend, colleague, family member etc in your place. Would you please communicate that to Nicoletta before the lesson starts? Grazie!</span></p>\n<p style="font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia1,Georgia,serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 140%;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">La Cucina del Sole maintains the right to cancel the workshops/courses in case there aren&rsquo;t enough participants. The money paid in advance by the participants will be returned on the original bank account or it will be possible to participate to a next course/workshop.</span></p>\n<div id="txt_137">\n<p style="font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia1,Georgia,serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 140%;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">Special requirements: are you allergic for certain ingredients? Please tell that to Nicoletta so that she can make sure the menu fits your requirements!</span></p>\n<p style="font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia1,Georgia,serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 140%;"><span style="font-size: 14px; color: #000101;">Of course La Cucina del Sole can organize a course just for a <strong>private group of friends, colleagues</strong> etc. (min. 8 and max. 80 participants). Please contact Nicoletta using the "<strong><a href="../../contact" target="_blank"><span style="color: #000101;">Contact</span></a></strong>" page if you wish to organize such course or to register for an existing course.</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>', '9ad59b78f05d6110e79b4cd917628e6e.jpg', '', '0000-00-00', 1, 1, 0, '2013-12-15 13:52:27'),
(46, 222, 110, 'The basics of the Italian cuisine', '<h1 style="color: #ffffff; font-size: 26px; font-family: Georgia1,Georgia,serif; font-weight: bold; line-height: 160%;"><span style="color: #000101;">The basics of the Italian cuisine</span></h1>\n<div class="gmail_extra"><span style="color: #000101;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><strong><strong>(to see more text click on it and scroll down with PgDown or arrow)<br /></strong></strong></span><strong><br /></strong><strong>Course "Di16" on Tuesday 14/28 January and 11/25 February 2014</strong></span><br /><span style="color: #000101;"><strong>Course "Wo08" on Wednesday 15/29 January and 12/26 February 2014</strong>&nbsp;</span><br /><span style="font-size: 15px; color: #000101;"><strong>Course "Di17" on Tuesday 6/20 May and 3/17 June 2014</strong></span></div>\n<div class="gmail_extra"><span style="color: #000101;">&nbsp;</span></div>\n<div class="gmail_extra"><span style="font-size: 14px; color: #000101;"><strong>Lesson 1: Antipasti,&nbsp;</strong><strong>starters and nibbles&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></span><br /><span style="font-size: 14px; color: #000101;">Frittata (Italian omelet), meatballs in a classic tomato sauce, crespelle con pesto rosso e mozzarella (little cr&ecirc;pes with red pesto and mozzarella), focaccia with rosemary, crema di olive (olive tapenade), oven-roasted peppers, polenta crostini with gorgonzola and fried sage, crostini with basil-lemon ricotta and several other typically Italian starters, real classics of the Italian cuisine. The above-mentioned dishes can vary according to the different seasons.</span></div>\n<div class="gmail_extra"><span style="color: #000101;">&nbsp;</span></div>\n<div class="gmail_extra"><span style="font-size: 14px; color: #000101;"><strong>Lesson 2: Pasta, gnocchi and sauces&nbsp;</strong></span><br /><span style="font-size: 14px; color: #000101;">Pasta making (techniques, tips &amp; tricks, the best ingredients and variations, for example coloured or filled pasta etc),&nbsp;<strong>basic sauces&nbsp;</strong>(among which the&nbsp;<em>pesto alla genovese</em>&nbsp;and the classic&nbsp;<em>bolognese</em>), making<strong>&nbsp;potato gnocchi</strong>&nbsp;(dumplings).</span></div>\n<div class="gmail_extra"><span style="color: #000101;">&nbsp;</span></div>\n<div class="gmail_extra"><span style="font-size: 14px; color: #000101;"><strong>Lesson 3: Bread, risotto and special vegetables&nbsp;</strong></span><br /><span style="font-size: 14px; color: #000101;">Making&nbsp;<em>ciabatta</em>&nbsp;(basic bread making), making stock (vegetarian, meat), saffron risotto with&nbsp;<em>ossobuco alla milanese</em>&nbsp;(braised veal shank),&nbsp;<em>risotto alle verdure di stagione</em>&nbsp;(risotto with seasonal vegetables), special vegetables.</span></div>\n<div class="gmail_extra"><span style="color: #000101;">&nbsp;</span></div>\n<div class="gmail_extra"><span style="font-size: 14px; color: #000101;"><strong>Lesson 4:&nbsp;</strong><strong>Fish, fish and more fish!&nbsp;</strong></span><br /><span style="color: #000101;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">Recognizing fish, cleaning and filleting it, (fish fillets in spicy white wine sauce), preparing fish stock, cleaning and cooking squid (small filled squid), shrimp (fried shrimp in kataifi dough), sardines in the oven with garlic and herbs, cockles (<em>spaghetti alle vongole</em>).</span><span style="font-size: 14px;">Please take with you: your own apron plus a kitchen towel.</span><span style="font-size: 14px;">All cooking lessons start at 18.30 hrs and end around 22.30 hrs.&nbsp;</span></span></div>\n<div class="gmail_extra"><span style="color: #000101;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><br /></span><span style="font-size: 14px;"><strong>The price for this course is</strong>&nbsp;<strong>&euro; 295,00&nbsp;</strong>including wine, all other drinks and all printed recipes. You can also give this combination of 4 lessons as a present: buy a gift voucher for a 4-week course! Very soon more courses for the periodo Aug. - Dec. 2014. Keep on checking this website for dates.</span>&nbsp;<span style="font-size: 14px;"><strong>Groups:&nbsp;</strong>We work in groups with a minimum of 4 and a maximum of 14 participants.</span></span><br /><span style="color: #000101;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">In case you miss a lesson it&rsquo;s not possible to come to another workshop later on. If you can&rsquo;t participate to one specific lesson, you can send a friend, colleague, family member etc in your place. Would you please communicate that to Nicoletta before the lesson starts? Grazie!</span><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-collapse: separate; font-family: ''American Typewriter''; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; border-spacing: 0px; font-size: medium;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-collapse: separate; font-family: ''American Typewriter''; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; border-spacing: 0px; font-size: medium;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">La Cucina del Sole maintains the right to cancel the workshops/courses in case there aren&rsquo;t enough participants. The money paid in advance by the participants will be returned on the original bank account or it will be possible to participate to a next course/workshop.</span></span></span></span>\n<p id="txt_134"><span style="color: #000101;">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<span style="font-size: 14px; color: #000101;">Special requirements: are you allergic for certain ingredients? Please tell that to Nicoletta so that she can make sure the menu fits your requirements!</span>\n<div id="txt_139"><span style="font-size: 14px; color: #000101;">Of course La Cucina del Sole can organize a course just for a private group of friends, colleagues etc. (min. 8 and max. 80 participants). Please contact Nicoletta using the "<strong><a href="../../contact" target="_blank"><span style="color: #000101;">Contact</span></a></strong>" page if you wish to organize such course or to register for an existing course.</span></div>\n</div>', 'b9a842385809e5c084470b2a323db3ce.jpg', '', '0000-00-00', 1, 0, 0, '2013-12-15 13:55:43');
