(119, 214, 106, 'Christmas', '<h1 style="margin: 0px 0px 40px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: Georgia; font-size: 30px; line-height: 19px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #b72025; background-color: #fbaa3e;">The Italian Christmas menu</h1>\n<p style="margin-bottom: 15px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: Georgia; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #000101; background-color: #fbaa3e;"><br /><span style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">Like every year we make a special menu for the &ldquo;warmest&rdquo; days of the year. Lots of wonderful&nbsp;<strong>Italian dishes</strong><strong>&nbsp;expressely made for Christmas.</strong><br /><br />Our Italian Christmas menu</span><strong>:&nbsp;</strong><span style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">rotolo di pasta ripieno (<strong>stuffed pasta roll&nbsp;</strong>with ricotta, Parmesan cheese and spinach), spezzatino di cinghiale alla toscana (<strong>Tuscan stew with wildboar&nbsp;</strong>in red wine with mushrooms, vegetables and spices),&nbsp;<strong>potato tartlets</strong>&nbsp;with pancetta and smoked scamorza cheese,&nbsp;<strong>pea and ricotta fritters</strong>, a special pudding made with&nbsp;<strong>panettone</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>baci di dama</strong>&nbsp;cookies to dip in our coffee or tea.</span></p>\n<p style="margin-bottom: 15px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: Georgia; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #000101; background-color: #fbaa3e;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="margin-bottom: 15px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: Georgia; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #000101; background-color: #fbaa3e;"><strong><span style="margin: 0px; p